thread.title_full: Texas A&M beats out Texas for four-star McKinney North DE Justin Madubuike | Dallas Morning News

author: EJ Holland
title: beats out Texas for four-star McKinney North DE Justin Madubuike
text:
Texas A&M's defensive line is only getting better.
On Friday afternoon, the Aggies picked up a verbal commitment from one of the country's top defensive ends in McKinney North's Justin Madubuike, SportsDayHS' Preseason Defensive Player of the Year.
Madubuike announced his commitment on Twitter.
Happy to say that I have committed to The Texas A&M Aggies! #Gig 'em #ItsAboutUs
â€” Justin Madubuike (@JMadubuike15) September 18, 2015 A four-star prospect, Madubuike committed to Texas A&M over offers from Alabama, Baylor, Ohio State, Oklahoma, Texas, USC and a number of other top programs.
Texas A&M and Texas were considered his two favorites.
At 6-foot-3, 255 pounds, Madubuike is ranked as the No. 7 strong-side defensive end in the country and No. 16 overall prospect in the state, according to 247Sports Composite.
Texas A&M now has 15 verbal commits in its 2016 class. He is the second defensive end to pledge, joining four-star Cibolo Steele recruit Mark Jackson.
